title: Sounds of African Forests and Savannas
description:
These twelve atmosphere recordings from Africa are made up of the sounds of birds -- from the tuneful Robin Chats to the croaking Turacos and the laughing and crying of Hornbills -- of mammals, from lions and elephants to hippopotamus and fruit bats -- of frogs and toads, and of insects. Together they make up 70 minutes of uninterrupted stereo concerts.

Recorded by Jean C. Roche
